00:15:51.070 --> 00:15:53.130
So let's turn these
into an opportunity

00:15:53.130 --> 00:15:55.380
and try to deliver the
best experience based

00:15:55.380 --> 00:15:59.860
on relevant factors such
as SOC, RAM, or CPU.

00:15:59.860 --> 00:16:03.330
But during this process, there's
one key thing to remember,

00:16:03.330 --> 00:16:05.960
which is essentially
to think big.

00:16:05.960 --> 00:16:08.240
And what I mean by
think big is just

00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:12.950
let's try to include as many
devices by default as possible.

00:16:12.950 --> 00:16:15.530
Excluding devices should
be a temporary measure

00:16:15.530 --> 00:16:19.950
until some of these
bugs are fixed.

00:16:19.950 --> 00:16:22.750
Let's look at the
device detail page.

00:16:22.750 --> 00:16:25.130
The device detail
page is a feature

00:16:25.130 --> 00:16:26.900
