00:16:52.640 --> 00:16:55.250
Lastly, I wanted
to highlight also

00:16:55.250 --> 00:16:57.490
some interesting information
that the device detail

00:16:57.490 --> 00:16:59.480
page is providing--

00:16:59.480 --> 00:17:01.610
essentially, the number
of active devices

00:17:01.610 --> 00:17:06.060
in this particular game,
the average rating,

00:17:06.060 --> 00:17:08.930
and the revenues generated
by inner purchases

00:17:08.930 --> 00:17:13.280
or subscriptions
in the last month.

00:17:13.280 --> 00:17:17.810
So what some of the developers
are saying about this.

00:17:17.810 --> 00:17:21.440
So Digital Legends, a mobile
developer from Barcelona,

00:17:21.440 --> 00:17:26.660
they actually launched a very
popular game, "Respawnables",

00:17:26.660 --> 00:17:28.940
which was launched in 2014.

00:17:28.940 --> 00:17:31.730
And since then, they have seen
more than 30 million installs,

00:17:31.730 --> 00:17:34.250
and what is more important,
more than 2 billion battles

00:17:34.250 --> 00:17:36.710
played by the players.

00:17:36.710 --> 00:17:39.350
So Digital Legends, two
or three times a week,

00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:41.690
they check the device catalog.

00:17:41.690 --> 00:17:43.650
And essentially,
they do three things.

00:17:43.650 --> 00:17:45.530
The first one, they
exclude those devices

00:17:45.530 --> 00:17:48.980
that do not meet the minimum
requirements in order

00:17:48.980 --> 00:17:52.010
to deliver a great
user experience.

00:17:52.010 --> 00:17:54.410
Then second, they
isolate the bugs.

00:17:54.410 --> 00:17:59.360
And then third, they prioritize
device support and, as well,

00:17:59.360 --> 00:18:01.320
these bug fixes.

00:18:01.320 --> 00:18:04.040
So thanks to this
feature, Digital Legends

00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:07.730
has seen an increase in the
user experience and ratings,

00:18:07.730 --> 00:18:13.050
as well on the overall quality
and performance of the game.

00:18:13.050 --> 00:18:15.830
So in conclusion, I wanted
to highlight three things

00:18:15.830 --> 00:18:17.220
to remember.

00:18:17.220 --> 00:18:20.300
So the first one, think big,
and support as many devices

00:18:20.300 --> 00:18:21.570
as possible.

00:18:21.570 --> 00:18:24.340
Second, if we have to
exclude some devices,

00:18:24.340 --> 00:18:28.370
try to do it in a temporary way,
so we can fix all those bugs

00:18:28.370 --> 00:18:31.430
and increase our chances
to reach a bigger audience.

00:18:31.430 --> 00:18:34.310
And then last, use
the device detail page

00:18:34.310 --> 00:18:37.010
to get very relevant
information, such as,

00:18:37.010 --> 00:18:40.970
for example, the unsupported
reason, or the average revenues

00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:43.160
or average rating.

00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:46.890
And with this, let's move
onto the next functionality

00:18:46.890 --> 00:18:48.060
feature--

00:18:48.060 --> 00:18:50.170
preregistration.

00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:53.830
We all know that, in
gaming, creating excitement

00:18:53.830 --> 00:18:55.750
before even launch
is increasingly

00:18:55.750 --> 00:18:57.890
critical and popular.

00:18:57.890 --> 00:19:01.690
So the preregistration
feature has two benefits.

00:19:01.690 --> 00:19:03.590
As a player, it's clear.

00:19:03.590 --> 00:19:06.770
You can pre-register, and then
when the game is launched,

00:19:06.770 --> 00:19:09.890
you will receive a notification
to install the game.

00:19:09.890 --> 00:19:12.730
We all know that in certain
type of games, multiplayer,

00:19:12.730 --> 00:19:15.140
social games, competitive
games in general,

00:19:15.140 --> 00:19:21.970
it's critical to get
on early into the game.

00:19:21.970 --> 00:19:23.960
However, from a
developer perspective,

00:19:23.960 --> 00:19:27.390
I can see that there's
two main benefits here.

00:19:27.390 --> 00:19:30.440
The first one is you can start
marketing early and capture

00:19:30.440 --> 00:19:32.600
the audience interest.

00:19:32.600 --> 00:19:35.420
As well, by monitoring
the pre-reg count,

00:19:35.420 --> 00:19:38.980
we have an indication of the
influx of users at launch.

00:19:38.980 --> 00:19:41.510
And we can plan ahead not
only from a server side,

00:19:41.510 --> 00:19:44.020
but also like marketing.

00:19:44.020 --> 00:19:46.910
So let's look at a case study.

00:19:46.910 --> 00:19:49.290
Nexon is a Korean
developer and the creator

00:19:49.290 --> 00:19:52.290
of some popular games, in
particular "Durango Wild

00:19:52.290 --> 00:19:54.810
Lands", which was
launched in Korea the 25th

00:19:54.810 --> 00:19:57.000
of January, 2018.

00:19:57.000 --> 00:19:58.890
So they started
the pre-reg process

00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:01.440
six weeks before
launching the game.

00:20:01.440 --> 00:20:05.730
And during this time, they saw
2.5 million preregistration

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:06.850
users.

00:20:06.850 --> 00:20:10.350
Out of those 2.5 million
users, pre-reg users,

00:20:10.350 --> 00:20:16.150
46% were coming from the Play
pre-registration feature.

00:20:16.150 --> 00:20:17.670
And what is very
interesting here

00:20:17.670 --> 00:20:19.530
is that the day
seven conversion,

00:20:19.530 --> 00:20:22.440
meaning from launch date
until the day seven,

00:20:22.440 --> 00:20:25.950
the first week, the conversion
for Play pre-reg users

00:20:25.950 --> 00:20:30.060
was about 70%, which
is seven times higher

00:20:30.060 --> 00:20:32.077
than the other sources.

00:20:32.077 --> 00:20:34.410
So as Kiki [? Heelman, ?] the
head of platform relations

00:20:34.410 --> 00:20:39.050
says, "Google preregistration
is essentially a very effective

00:20:39.050 --> 00:20:41.270
marketing tool."

00:20:41.270 --> 00:20:43.700
So how is Nexon using
for other games?

00:20:43.700 --> 00:20:47.210
So Nexon has launched
20 games in 2017

00:20:47.210 --> 00:20:49.190
and has used the
pre-registration feature

00:20:49.190 --> 00:20:52.940
in 10 games last year.

00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:55.880
They saw a 50% conversion
from pre-reg users

00:20:55.880 --> 00:21:00.070
to actual users
downloading this game.

00:21:00.070 --> 00:21:03.500
They have seen also that
the CPIs are quite lower.

00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:08.170
They're 60% lower in pre-launch
than in post-lunch period.

00:21:08.170 --> 00:21:10.810
And as such, this has led
to a decision to allocate

00:21:10.810 --> 00:21:15.340
the marketing budget 50%
to the pre-launch state ,

00:21:15.340 --> 00:21:16.838
rather than in post-launch.

00:21:19.980 --> 00:21:22.920
So far, the preregistration
pilot has been very successful.

00:21:22.920 --> 00:21:26.710
In 2017, we've seen numbers,
such as more than 50 developers

00:21:26.710 --> 00:21:29.490
using this
functionality, as well,

00:21:29.490 --> 00:21:32.850
200 million players registering,
and 100 million players

00:21:32.850 --> 00:21:35.550
actually downloading
those games, and then

00:21:35.550 --> 00:21:40.380
a total of 400 launches across
both small and big developers.

00:21:40.380 --> 00:21:42.280
Indeed, this is exciting.

00:21:42.280 --> 00:21:44.850
But what is even more
exciting is to know that,

00:21:44.850 --> 00:21:46.950
today, we are
announcing that pre-reg

00:21:46.950 --> 00:21:51.280
is becoming available to
all developers very soon.

00:21:51.280 --> 00:21:53.350
So what are some of
the things that we

00:21:53.350 --> 00:21:55.930
need to take into account
if we want to have

00:21:55.930 --> 00:21:58.300
a good experience with pre-reg?

00:21:58.300 --> 00:22:01.540
So three things, as well,
that I wanted to remember.

00:22:01.540 --> 00:22:04.630
So the first is allow some
time to build excitement.

00:22:04.630 --> 00:22:08.080
So in between three
to six weeks is enough

00:22:08.080 --> 00:22:11.160
in order to gather all
this audience interest.

00:22:11.160 --> 00:22:13.000
But as well, use
all the channels

00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:16.390
that you have available in
order to build that excitement,

00:22:16.390 --> 00:22:20.470
for example, media, communities,
forums, your own website.

00:22:20.470 --> 00:22:22.420
And across all
these channels, make

00:22:22.420 --> 00:22:24.820
sure that you have
a clear action--

00:22:24.820 --> 00:22:29.830
in this case, preregister
in Google Play.

00:22:29.830 --> 00:22:33.510
With this in mind, let's
jump into the last tool,

00:22:33.510 --> 00:22:35.550
which is country targeting.

00:22:35.550 --> 00:22:38.520
Country targeting is
a very powerful tool.

00:22:38.520 --> 00:22:41.020
And essentially, it
allows two things.

00:22:41.020 --> 00:22:44.010
So first, we can have
different tracks per country.

00:22:44.010 --> 00:22:46.860
And then we can run
separate closed, open tests

00:22:46.860 --> 00:22:50.050
or production in a
specific geography.

00:22:50.050 --> 00:22:52.520
This is very useful
as the quote mentions,

00:22:52.520 --> 00:22:54.460
for soft launching processes.

00:22:54.460 --> 00:22:57.400
Where for example, we want
to have one particular region

00:22:57.400 --> 00:23:02.080
in production to test user
acquisition or monetization.

00:23:02.080 --> 00:23:04.830
Secondly, it's key during
launch because we can use

00:23:04.830 --> 00:23:06.742
a staged rollout per geography.

00:23:06.742 --> 00:23:08.200
And this means that
you can control

00:23:08.200 --> 00:23:10.000
the rollout in
different countries,

00:23:10.000 --> 00:23:13.310
and then monitor which users
are getting into the app.

00:23:13.310 --> 00:23:17.600
This allows us to test server
performance or user feedback.

00:23:17.600 --> 00:23:19.750
So let's look at how
some developers are

00:23:19.750 --> 00:23:22.880
using this functionality.

00:23:22.880 --> 00:23:26.340
So Wargaming, Ukrainian
developer and behind the game

00:23:26.340 --> 00:23:29.130
"World of Warships Blitz",
they launched this game

00:23:29.130 --> 00:23:31.830
in January, 2018, as well.

00:23:31.830 --> 00:23:34.740
And the game has already seen
more than 3 million installs

00:23:34.740 --> 00:23:36.210
in Google Play.

00:23:36.210 --> 00:23:38.880
By the way, 100
million ships destroyed

00:23:38.880 --> 00:23:41.610
and more than 15 million
