00:23:54.880 --> 00:23:57.990
This soft launch period
took about six months,

00:23:57.990 --> 00:24:00.490
and they divided
it in three stages.

00:24:00.490 --> 00:24:03.420
So the first stage, they select
a few number of countries.

00:24:03.420 --> 00:24:05.850
And they were testing
things like stability--

00:24:05.850 --> 00:24:09.930
so crash rates, monetization,
lifetime value, and CPI--

00:24:09.930 --> 00:24:13.230
and then engagement, which is
user engagement and duration

00:24:13.230 --> 00:24:14.820
of the games.

00:24:14.820 --> 00:24:19.680
On the second stage, they opened
up to a few more countries,

00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:23.310
and they were testing
mostly server capacity

00:24:23.310 --> 00:24:26.740
and ensuring the
stability of the game.

00:24:26.740 --> 00:24:28.920
And then on the
third stage, they

00:24:28.920 --> 00:24:31.050
opened up to already
more countries

00:24:31.050 --> 00:24:35.790
across all continents with the
intent of testing monetization,

00:24:35.790 --> 00:24:37.560
mostly.

00:24:37.560 --> 00:24:40.890
So lastly during
this whole process,

00:24:40.890 --> 00:24:44.340
Wargaming was testing,
as well, and monitoring

00:24:44.340 --> 00:24:46.230
the ratings and the
reviews and reacting

00:24:46.230 --> 00:24:49.330
based on the user feedback.

00:24:49.330 --> 00:24:52.500
So in conclusion, regarding
country targeting,

00:24:52.500 --> 00:24:54.370
two things to remember today.

00:24:54.370 --> 00:24:57.090
So the first one is like we
can use country targeting

00:24:57.090 --> 00:25:01.380
during soft launch, but also
during the open and closed

00:25:01.380 --> 00:25:06.510
Beta test processes, as well as
during even like future updates

00:25:06.510 --> 00:25:08.810
