you can go to this
talk tomorrow morning.

00:28:00.010 --> 00:28:03.010
Next, we'll talk about
Google Play Instant.

00:28:03.010 --> 00:28:05.620
Growing your game involves
getting users excited about it.

00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:08.890
And a great way to do that is to
give them a quick and easy way

00:28:08.890 --> 00:28:10.510
to experience it.

00:28:10.510 --> 00:28:13.480
For quick background, we
launched Instant Apps at I/O

00:28:13.480 --> 00:28:14.330
last year.

00:28:14.330 --> 00:28:16.640
And since then,
we've been very busy.

00:28:16.640 --> 00:28:18.370
There are more than
a billion devices

00:28:18.370 --> 00:28:19.960
that support Instant Apps.

00:28:19.960 --> 00:28:22.710
And we've improved our
tooling to make building

00:28:22.710 --> 00:28:24.740
Instant Apps even easier.

00:28:24.740 --> 00:28:26.380
And as you may have
heard, we announced

00:28:26.380 --> 00:28:30.370
that we're bringing Instant Apps
to games at GDC six weeks ago.

00:28:30.370 --> 00:28:32.160
And as of today,
Google Play Instant

00:28:32.160 --> 00:28:36.600
is now available to
all game developers.

00:28:36.600 --> 00:28:40.580
So why should you consider
making an instant game?

00:28:40.580 --> 00:28:43.370
Instant games allow players to
try your game before installing

00:28:43.370 --> 00:28:45.710
it and make it easy to
install the full game

00:28:45.710 --> 00:28:47.900
at the end of the instant
game experience using

00:28:47.900 --> 00:28:50.180
the install prompt API.

00:28:50.180 --> 00:28:52.100
Being able to try a
game before installing

00:28:52.100 --> 00:28:53.380
is a hit with players.

00:28:53.380 --> 00:28:55.550
And after publishing
their Instant game,

00:28:55.550 --> 00:28:59.140
Mighty Battles has seen a 19%
increase in acquisition rate.

00:29:01.900 --> 00:29:06.300
So what's the difference between
Instant Apps and Instant Games?

00:29:06.300 --> 00:29:08.670
What we've done is adapt
the Instant App frameworks

00:29:08.670 --> 00:29:12.930
so it better meets the needs
of game developers like you.

00:29:12.930 --> 00:29:14.670
There are three
things we've changed.

00:29:14.670 --> 00:29:17.760
We've increased the size
limit to 10 megabytes.

00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:19.560
We've enabled
progressive download

00:29:19.560 --> 00:29:24.480
of executable code and assets
using the [INAUDIBLE] API.

00:29:24.480 --> 00:29:27.090
And very importantly,
we've added full support

00:29:27.090 --> 00:29:29.100
for native code
and are integrating

00:29:29.100 --> 00:29:31.530
with game engines and Open GL.

00:29:31.530 --> 00:29:33.480
This means you can
use the same codebase

00:29:33.480 --> 00:29:38.100
and tools as your full game
to build your instant game.

00:29:38.100 --> 00:29:42.840
And by creating an instant game,
you open up a lot of surfaces.

00:29:42.840 --> 00:29:46.650
Players can experience instant
games directly from ads,

00:29:46.650 --> 00:29:49.620
in the Play Games app
arcade, via a link you

00:29:49.620 --> 00:29:52.590
can send with a messaging
app, and of course,

00:29:52.590 --> 00:29:55.270
in the Play Store.

00:29:55.270 --> 00:29:57.550
While we're on the topic
of Google Play Instant,

00:29:57.550 --> 00:30:00.790
we need to touch back just for
a moment on launching tools.

00:30:00.790 --> 00:30:03.250
Pre-reg is a very
successful program.

00:30:03.250 --> 00:30:04.780
And we're bringing
the Instant games

00:30:04.780 --> 00:30:07.720
to Play Store's
preregistration feature.

00:30:07.720 --> 00:30:09.670
Now players that
preregister can get

00:30:09.670 --> 00:30:12.160
a sneak preview of your game.

00:30:12.160 --> 00:30:13.690
And when you promote
preregistration

00:30:13.690 --> 00:30:16.690
through social media,
email, or on your website,

00:30:16.690 --> 00:30:18.400
users will be able
to play instantly

00:30:18.400 --> 00:30:20.020
from any Android device.

00:30:20.020 --> 00:30:24.320
It's an awesome way to introduce
your game to the world.

00:30:24.320 --> 00:30:25.870
To learn more about
Instant games,

00:30:25.870 --> 00:30:27.910
you can attend this
session on Thursday.

00:30:31.250 --> 00:30:34.250
Next, we'll look at engagement.

00:30:34.250 --> 00:30:37.250
Android Vitals is designed
to help you identify issues

00:30:37.250 --> 00:30:40.880
at scale so you can create
a better, more fluid, more

00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:44.870
optimized, and more engaging
experience for your players.

00:30:44.870 --> 00:30:47.330
There are a number of new
vitals features launching,

00:30:47.330 --> 00:30:49.370
including benchmarks
for all vitals,

00:30:49.370 --> 00:30:51.329
and new vitals, including
startup time, which

00:30:51.329 --> 00:30:53.120
were discussed in the
Android Vital session

00:30:53.120 --> 00:30:56.070
earlier this afternoon.

00:30:56.070 --> 00:30:58.050
Of particular interest
for game developers

00:30:58.050 --> 00:31:01.080
like you, are stability
and battery vitals.

00:31:01.080 --> 00:31:03.720
Stability vitals include
A and R's and crashes.

00:31:03.720 --> 00:31:07.770
And batteries include stuck wake
locks and excessive wakeups.

00:31:07.770 --> 00:31:10.500
We're now showing these
vitals against a bad behavior

00:31:10.500 --> 00:31:11.880
threshold.

00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:14.160
Exhibiting bad
behavior in vitals

00:31:14.160 --> 00:31:17.490
will negatively affect the
user experience in your game

00:31:17.490 --> 00:31:20.490
and can result in bad ratings
and poor discoverability

00:31:20.490 --> 00:31:22.100
in the Play Store.

00:31:22.100 --> 00:31:24.280
We also have vitals for
rendering and startup time,

00:31:24.280 --> 00:31:26.742
though, these are
informative at this point.

00:31:26.742 --> 00:31:28.200
And with the new
vitals benchmarks,

00:31:28.200 --> 00:31:32.800
you can see how you stack
up against similar games.

00:31:32.800 --> 00:31:34.870
It's important to know
that Android Vitals is

00:31:34.870 --> 00:31:37.640
a powerful tool not
just for app developers,

00:31:37.640 --> 00:31:39.700
but for game developers too.

00:31:39.700 --> 00:31:42.550
Using Vitals, game
developer, Kiloo,

00:31:42.550 --> 00:31:46.090
whose game "Subway Surfers"
just passed 1 billion installs

00:31:46.090 --> 00:31:49.735
on Google Play, was able to make
drastic improvements to their A

00:31:49.735 --> 00:31:53.545
and R rate, reducing it from
around 2% to below 0.1%.

00:31:57.270 --> 00:32:01.020
So to help you ensure your
users enjoy playing your game,

00:32:01.020 --> 00:32:03.660
how should you be thinking
about using Vitals in your day

00:32:03.660 --> 00:32:05.130
to day?

00:32:05.130 --> 00:32:08.490
Keep an eye on A and
R's, crashes, wake locks,

00:32:08.490 --> 00:32:11.190
and wake ups, which will be
easier with the notifications

00:32:11.190 --> 00:32:13.890
and alerts built
into Play Console.

00:32:13.890 --> 00:32:16.157
And use the Vitals dashboard
as part of your toolkit

00:32:16.157 --> 00:32:17.115
to chase down problems.

00:32:19.810 --> 00:32:21.560
Now, we wanted to share
with you something

00:32:21.560 --> 00:32:22.829
we've been working on.

00:32:22.829 --> 00:32:24.620
It's not ready for
general consumption yet.

00:32:24.620 --> 00:32:25.670
That's coming.

00:32:25.670 --> 00:32:29.720
But we're excited to be working
to bring LiveOps to play.

00:32:29.720 --> 00:32:32.240
We are creating new
experiences in the store

00:32:32.240 --> 00:32:34.520
and in the Play Games
app to show players

00:32:34.520 --> 00:32:37.550
the events that are
happening now in their games.

00:32:37.550 --> 00:32:39.550
This is proving very
popular with players,

00:32:39.550 --> 00:32:43.590
and we're going to continue
exploring in this direction.

00:32:43.590 --> 00:32:47.610
And finally, let's
move on to revenue.

00:32:47.610 --> 00:32:50.420
Google Play has had
subscriptions since 2012,

00:32:50.420 --> 00:32:52.560
but they've mostly been
the domain of subscription

00:32:52.560 --> 00:32:54.220
for access apps.

00:32:54.220 --> 00:32:58.560
Games typically monetize through
IAPs in ads or are paid games.

00:32:58.560 --> 00:33:00.720
But a number of developers
have been experimenting

00:33:00.720 --> 00:33:02.130
with subscriptions,
and we wanted

00:33:02.130 --> 00:33:04.740
to share their experiences.

00:33:04.740 --> 00:33:06.870
You may be wondering,
what's the business case

00:33:06.870 --> 00:33:10.470
of adding subscriptions
when I already have IAP?

00:33:10.470 --> 00:33:12.370
Developers who
implement subscriptions

00:33:12.370 --> 00:33:15.270
report an increase in
engagement and retention

00:33:15.270 --> 00:33:17.730
not just for the subscribers,
but for their overall user

00:33:17.730 --> 00:33:19.860
base, as well, as you can
see from Monster Strike's

00:33:19.860 --> 00:33:23.070
experience with "MonPass."

00:33:23.070 --> 00:33:27.270
Many, including Scopely, also
notice minimal cannibalization

00:33:27.270 --> 00:33:29.760
of IAP, resulting
in incremental gains

00:33:29.760 --> 00:33:33.410
to overall revenue driven by
both subscriptions and IAP.

00:33:36.640 --> 00:33:38.970
Another developer who's found
successful subscriptions

00:33:38.970 --> 00:33:43.210
is Network in "Legendary
Game of Heroes."

00:33:43.210 --> 00:33:46.429
They use subscriptions for
their VIP loyalty program.

00:33:46.429 --> 00:33:48.970
This program has proved popular
with players, as you can see,

00:33:48.970 --> 00:33:50.980
and had created a
new revenue stream

00:33:50.980 --> 00:33:54.100
for "Legendary Game of Heroes"
with strong positive impact

00:33:54.100 --> 00:33:57.120
on overall revenue.

00:33:57.120 --> 00:33:59.730
There are two best practices
in using subscriptions

00:33:59.730 --> 00:34:01.740
to provide value to players--

00:34:01.740 --> 00:34:04.920
loyalty programs for your high
value users and a new access

00:34:04.920 --> 00:34:09.000
point to premium experience
for traditional non-buyers.

00:34:09.000 --> 00:34:11.280
The target audience
will influence how you

00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:13.590
choose to design your offering.

00:34:13.590 --> 00:34:15.810
Some examples of a
VIP loyalty program

00:34:15.810 --> 00:34:20.730
features include exclusive
or early access to content,

00:34:20.730 --> 00:34:24.760
special in-game VIP status
and title, or a bonus

00:34:24.760 --> 00:34:27.357
payout with each purchase.

00:34:27.357 --> 00:34:29.190
This is the most popular
subscription design

00:34:29.190 --> 00:34:30.719
we've seen so far
and, as you can

00:34:30.719 --> 00:34:33.120
see from Ludia's "Jurassic
World, The Game,"

00:34:33.120 --> 00:34:33.780
implement here.

00:34:36.400 --> 00:34:38.290
Developers have also
found that subscriptions

00:34:38.290 --> 00:34:41.989
can be effective in converting
traditional non-buyers.

00:34:41.989 --> 00:34:45.010
These players are motivated by
getting a good financial deal.

00:34:45.010 --> 00:34:46.929
You can see Network's
implementation here,

00:34:46.929 --> 00:34:48.940
which is a VIP
loyalty program aimed

00:34:48.940 --> 00:34:51.969
at these traditional non-buyers.

00:34:51.969 --> 00:34:54.699
Of course, as with any
monetization system,

00:34:54.699 --> 00:34:56.719
be aware of potential downsides.

00:34:56.719 --> 00:34:59.830
And keep a close pulse of
player feedback and community

00:34:59.830 --> 00:35:02.490
sentiment.

00:35:02.490 --> 00:35:04.620
To help you with your
subscription program,

00:35:04.620 --> 00:35:08.010
Google Play has a very robust
subscriptions infrastructure

00:35:08.010 --> 00:35:10.290
with a lot of rich features.

00:35:10.290 --> 00:35:13.310
We support you with billing
tools and analytics insight

00:35:13.310 --> 00:35:16.020
reports throughout the
entire user funnel.

00:35:16.020 --> 00:35:19.020
And we can take care of
useful subscription features,

00:35:19.020 --> 00:35:24.090
such as flexible billing,
free trials, account hold,

00:35:24.090 --> 00:35:26.310
so that you can focus on
testing and implementing

00:35:26.310 --> 00:35:30.394
an effective in-game
subscription design.

00:35:30.394 --> 00:35:31.810
To learn more about
subscriptions,

00:35:31.810 --> 00:35:33.880
you can watch the
recording of this session

00:35:33.880 --> 00:35:35.570
from earlier this afternoon.

